  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "22 against 9 petitions",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "9 petitions have been filed before the Supreme Court today (18th) claiming that certain clauses of the 22nd Constitution Amendment Bill submitted to the Parliament are contrary to the Constitution, and to issue an order to pass it by a special number of MPs and a referendum.",
        "9 people including Dr. Gunadasa Amarasekara, General Secretary of Praideh Peramuna, lawyer Nagananda Kodithuvakku, have filed these petitions before the Supreme Court."
      ],
